think all their Hours away , And still think on , till the confining Clay Fall off , and nothing's left behind Of drossy Earth , nothing to clog the Mind , Or hinder its Ascent to those bright Forms above , Those glorious Beings whose exalted Sense Transcends the highest Flights of human Wit

the Dance : Sometime the earthly Particles aspired , And upward forced their way , While the spirituous Parts retired , And near the Centre lay Depressed and sunk , till by the next Remove They disengaged , and got above , But could not long the impelling Shock sustain , By Turns they rise , by Turns they fell again
the spirituous Parts retired , And near the Centre

Curse Heaven , our selves , our Friends , our Fate , And new , more pungent
Dangers we despise , And present Evils
